{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Please place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]) -->
{{High-use}}
{{Twinkle standard installation}}

== Usage ==
Add {{Tlx|Unreliable sources|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}} to the top of the article, below any [[WP:HAT|hatnotes]].

Consider tagging any specific statements with potentially unreliable sources with {{Tlx|Verify credibility|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}} before tagging the whole article with this template.

===Parameters===
;Date (''required''{{px2}})
: {{para|date|(current month and year, as in {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}})}}
;Some
: {{para|some|yes}} is the default and begins the template with "Some of this article's listed sources..."
:{{para|some|no}} begins the template with "Some or all of this article's listed sources..."
;Unnamed
: {{para|1|section}} changes "article" to "section" in the text.
;Imdb
: {{para|imdb|yes}} adds the text "It includes attribution to IMDb, which may not be a reliable source for information."
;Small
: {{para|small|left}} makes the template box small and aligned to the left.

== Redirects ==
The following templates redirect here:
* {{tl|unrel}}
* {{tl|Unreliable}}
*{{tl|Badsources}}
*{{tl|Reliable sources}}
*{{tl|Reliable-sources}}
*{{tl|Reliablesources}}
*{{tl|Unreliablesources}}
*{{tl|Better sources needed}}
== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "Use this template to indicate that some of an article's listed sources may not be reliable.",
	"format": "inline",
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "The month and year that the template was placed (in full). \"May 2025\" inserts the current month and year automatically.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"example": "January 2013",
			"suggested": true
		},
		"some": {
			"label": "Some or all?",
			"description": "Enter \"n\", \"no\", \"false\", \"off\" or \"0\" to change \"Some\" to \"Some or all\".",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "n",
			"example": "n"
		},
		"1": {
			"label": "Affected area",
			"description": "Text to replace the word \"article\", usually \"section\"",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "section",
			"example": "section"
		},
		"imdb": {
			"label": "Includes IMDb?",
			"description": "Adds the text \"It includes attribution to IMDb, which may not be a reliable source for information.\"",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "y",
			"example": "y"
		},
		"small": {
			"label": "Make template small",
			"description": "Enter \"left\" here to make the template box small and aligned to the left.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "left",
			"example": "left"
		}
	},
	"paramOrder": [
		"date",
		"some",
		"1",
		"imdb",
		"small"
	]
}
</templatedata>

== See also ==
* {{tl|Unreliable source inline}} (redirects to <nowiki>{{Unreliable source?}}</nowiki>)
* {{tl|Better source needed}}
* {{tl|No reliable sources}}
* [[Wikipedia:Template messages/Cleanup]]
* [[Wikipedia:Template messages/Sources of articles]]

